<paragraph id="8BB236EBFFA4FFCA1FC8FE84FF6A4B8E" blockId="50.[151,1437,325,1395]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis: Eyes touching for distance equal to 4.5–5 times ocellar triangle. Inner surstylus with a projection at base ventrally; SES with 20–22 tiny spines, lower border distinct; phallic guide broadening in the middle, pointed at apex.</paragraph>
