<subSubSection id="C3176560FFA4FFCA1FC8FD80FEC24F65" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB236EBFFA4FFCA1FC8FD80FF694872" blockId="50.[151,1437,325,1395]" box="[151,208,577,601]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Male</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236EBFFA4FFCA1FC8FDA4FD1F48ED" blockId="50.[151,1437,325,1395]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B979EAF9FFA4FFCA1FC8FDA4FF6D4856" box="[151,212,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Head</emphasis>
. Third antennal segment acute; brown [based on PT]. Face greyish pollinose. Frons, lower part greyish pollinose on the sides, black in the middle; eyes touching for distance equal to 4.5-5 times ocellar triangle. Occiput, upper half brownish pollinose, lower half grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236EBFFA4FFCA1FC8FD10FE19491A" blockId="50.[151,1437,325,1395]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B979EAF9FFA4FFCA1FC8FD10FF5148C2" box="[151,232,721,745]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Thorax</emphasis>
. Humeri light brown. Mesonotum (viewed obliquely from front) brownish pollinose; greyish from the side. Scutellum brownish pollinose, with short, pale brown hairs. Dorsocentral hairs weakly developed. Halter, knob dark brown, stem paler.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236EBFFA4FFCA1FC8FCFFFA3949E8" blockId="50.[151,1437,325,1395]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
Legs. Trochanters and base of femora brown, femora black, knees, tibiae, tarsal segments, pale brown [no t3 on 
<typeStatus id="54B68849FFA4FFCA1FC8FCA3FF6E4951" box="[151,215,866,890]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">types</typeStatus>
], last segment black. Ventroapical row of 4–5 very small spines on f1; 10–12 short, stout on f2; no spines on 3rd femur. Subapical (distal) spines on first four tibiae missing. Anteromedial hairs on 3rd tibia [no 3. leg on 
<typeStatus id="54B68849FFA4FFCA1FC8FC6AFF6149E8" box="[151,216,939,963]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">types</typeStatus>
]. Hind trochanter with minute white hairs on ventral side. Pulvilli slightly smaller than last tarsal segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236EBFFA4FFCA1FC8FC0FFCE24E05" blockId="50.[151,1437,325,1395]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
Wing. Long, compared to body, damaged on 
<typeStatus id="54B68849FFA4FFCA1DC2FC0EFD6249CC" box="[669,731,975,999]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">types</typeStatus>
. Fourth costal section (probably) equal to third costal section. Cross-vein R-M almost in the middle of discal cell [PT: just beyond 1/3, near basal 2/ 
<quantity id="4CF59B0EFFA4FFCA1B09FC33FB394E21" box="[1110,1152,1010,1034]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
original description], dm elongated. Pterostigma fully coloured. Hairs on tegula missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236EBFFA4FFCA1FC8FBFAFC684E5D" blockId="50.[151,1437,325,1395]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B979EAF9FFA4FFCA1FC8FBFAFEB84E78" box="[151,257,1083,1107]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Abdomen</emphasis>
. [dissected in HT] Hairs dispersed, short and weakly developed. Seven dark, strong bristles laterally on first tergite. Postabdomen in dorsal view [dissected]: (T6, S7, EP) visible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236EBFFA4FFCA1FC8FB43FC664F01" blockId="50.[151,1437,325,1395]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
Genitalia (damaged on HT, lost on PT). Surstyli both broken, but not fused with EP (
<figureCitation id="13362A6EFFA4FFCA1B1AFB43FB144EB1" box="[1093,1197,1154,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1875,1898]" captionTargetBox="[282,1301,198,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-112@48.[270,1316,177,1852]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 16. Male genitalia of Eudorylas brandbergensis sp. nov. (A–F) and E. conformis (G–K).—A: outer surstylus with phallic guide and outer gonopod, lateral view, B: dorsal view, C: inner surstylus, lateral view, D: surstyli, dorsal view, E: sperm pump with ejaculatory apodeme, F: ventral view with phallic guide and phallus (without ST8), G: outer surstylus with phallic guide, phallus and outer gonopod, lateral view, H: surstyli (damaged), dorsal view, I: inner surstylus, lateral view, J: dorsal view, K: ventral view with phallic guide, phallus, sperm pump and ejaculatory apodeme (without ST8). Scale bars: 0.1 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6039192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6039192/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 16H</figureCitation>
), inner surstylus with a projection at base ventrally; epandrium deformed; ST 
<specimenCount id="9D0BFD62FFA4FFCA1C5CFB67FC8C4E95" box="[771,821,1190,1214]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CF59B0EFFA4FFCA1C5CFB67FC894E95" box="[771,816,1190,1214]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="8.0">8 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
a. not visible (
<figureCitation id="13362A6EFFA4FFCA1C8DFB67FB974E95" box="[978,1070,1190,1214]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1875,1898]" captionTargetBox="[282,1301,198,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-112@48.[270,1316,177,1852]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 16. Male genitalia of Eudorylas brandbergensis sp. nov. (A–F) and E. conformis (G–K).—A: outer surstylus with phallic guide and outer gonopod, lateral view, B: dorsal view, C: inner surstylus, lateral view, D: surstyli, dorsal view, E: sperm pump with ejaculatory apodeme, F: ventral view with phallic guide and phallus (without ST8), G: outer surstylus with phallic guide, phallus and outer gonopod, lateral view, H: surstyli (damaged), dorsal view, I: inner surstylus, lateral view, J: dorsal view, K: ventral view with phallic guide, phallus, sperm pump and ejaculatory apodeme (without ST8). Scale bars: 0.1 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6039192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6039192/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 16J</figureCitation>
) cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C4B1AFFA4FFCA1B3EFB67FB4D4E95" author="Hardy" box="[1121,1268,1190,1214]" firstAuthor="Hardy" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="27 - 29" refId="ref87980" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1959 b) Dorilaidae (Diptera Cyclorrhapha) Addendum. Exploration Parc National Albert Mission G. F. de Witte, 95, 27 - 29." type="journal article" year="1959" yearSuffix="b">
