</bibRefCitation>
. SES with 20– 22 tiny spines, lower border distinct; gonopods not clear, probably very small; hypandrium not connected to EP; phallic guide broadening in the middle, pointed at apex (
<figureCitation id="13362A6EFFA4FFCA1C68FB2FFC774F2D" box="[823,974,1262,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="48.[151,250,1875,1898]" captionTargetBox="[282,1301,198,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-112@48.[270,1316,177,1852]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 16. Male genitalia of Eudorylas brandbergensis sp. nov. (A–F) and E. conformis (G–K).—A: outer surstylus with phallic guide and outer gonopod, lateral view, B: dorsal view, C: inner surstylus, lateral view, D: surstyli, dorsal view, E: sperm pump with ejaculatory apodeme, F: ventral view with phallic guide and phallus (without ST8), G: outer surstylus with phallic guide, phallus and outer gonopod, lateral view, H: surstyli (damaged), dorsal view, I: inner surstylus, lateral view, J: dorsal view, K: ventral view with phallic guide, phallus, sperm pump and ejaculatory apodeme (without ST8). Scale bars: 0.1 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6039192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6039192/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Figs 16K, G</figureCitation>
); phallus with membranes, short, trifid, branches curved; ejaculatory apodeme elongated, linear; sperm pump oval.
</paragraph>
